news.title: Defaulters face music, Nashik civic body collects Rs 75 lakh property tax
news.para: NMC officials said drums were played in front of the houses of 73 tax defaulters. Around 40 of the tax defaulters paid their tax dues amounting to Rs 74 crore to the civic body on the first

news.title: Kolkata: KMRC to redevelop 26 houses razed in Bowbazar cave-in zone
news.para: ​While 23 houses were pulled down after the first subsidence on August 31, 2019, three more houses were demolished after irreparable cracks developed in the subsidence in May this year.

news.title: Revival charges needed to restore cancelled Chandigarh housing board dwelling unit licences
news.para: In case allotment of a dwelling unit is cancelled due to non-payment of license fee, revival charges shall be calculated at 10% of the accumulated outstanding amount of license fee.

news.title: Indore civic body starts verifying building permission documents
news.para: As per civic body officials, an 80ft road has been planned by the civic body on this stretch with an aim to solve traffic jams and congestion problems.

news.title: Urban estate to come up on 2,000 acres in Ludhiana: Punjab housing minister
news.para: Glada is already in the process of acquiring around 2,000-acre site at Ladowal bypass in Bagga Kalan, Noorpur Bet, Garha and Gounspur villages.

news.title: RLDA to lease out railway land in Kerala's Kannur for commercial development
news.para: ​The authority has invited bids for leasing 4.93 acres of railway land near the Kannur railway station for 45 years, RLDA said in a release. The reserve price for the land parcel is Rs 22.6 crore.

news.title: Gujarat government drafts new impact fee ordinance for cities, towns
news.para: This will be the third instance since the early 2000s that the state government will bring out a law to regularize illegal construction.

news.title: ICRA assigns provisional AAA rating, stable outlook to Nexus Select Trust
news.para: This retail REIT will have an initial portfolio of 17 retail malls, 3 office spaces, 2 hotels and 1 solar power generation plant across the country. Nexus Select Trust received registration from the capital markets regulator the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) on September 15.

news.title: Pune: Transit oriented development impact review almost ready, few changes likely
news.para: ​​The FSI rate has been reduced from 60% to 30% for residential properties of the ready reckoner (RR) rates following the government’s approval to the relaxed TOD policy on roads that have a width of nine metre and more.

news.title: Purva Asset Management invests Rs 93 crore from its first alternative investment fund
news.para: The project coming up in Guduvanchery has a development potential of 1.3 million sq ft. This is puravankara’s second plotted development project in Chennai.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India net profit falls 88% in July-September 2022
news.para: Its total revenue from operation was down 12.21 per cent to Rs 506.05 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 576.47 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Dubai sets new record with sale of Palm Jumeirah mansion for $82 million
news.para: The villa, called Casa Del Sole, fetched $82.4 million when it was sold in July, according to its developer Alpago Properties. The firm declined to name the buyer, citing privacy concerns. The mansion was bought without a mortgage, according to partially redacted title deed seen by Bloomberg.

news.title: ACC posts Rs 87.32 crore net loss in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 4,057.08 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 6.42 per cent from Rs 3,812.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's pre-sales up 24% at Rs 337 crore in July-September 2022
news.para: During the quarter, the company acquired a land parcel spread over 7.25 acres in Mira Road’s Beverly Park locality through a joint development agreement. The project is estimated to have development potential of around 2.5 million sq ft built up area and revenue potential of around Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: Bowbazar: 30 buildings under watch, eight more may have to be evacuated
news.para: STUP Consultants Private Limited, which has been appointed by ITD to conduct structural assessment of buildings, has started studying the condition of houses, after the latest subsidence on Friday.
